<Author>scfcdave
<Content>Great value and handy for Clot Metro Station to City We booked a triple room and although the room was small it was perfectly adequate for us. We arrived at mid-day and were checked in promptly by a very pleasant receptionist who gave us a map of Barcelona and helped us with questions about transport and places to visit.The Clot Metro underground station is literally 2 minutes walk away and you are in the centre of Barcelona within 10 minutes and all the main attractions can be reached from here too. The hotel is ideally located as it is in a residential area although there is a busy main road at the end of the street.The hotel Albeniz is clean and the staff very pleasant, the breakfast is amazing for a small hotel and you can eat as much as you want. The rooms have a mini-bar fridge which is useful and satelite TV with Sky News and Canal+ which was great for watching Spanish football!We would definitely stay here again especially at the excellent price which worked out at 拢80 per night for the room and breakfast for 3 people and it is a good base from which to travel around the vibrant city of Barcelona. 
