<Author>WelshTaff
<Content>Good 3 Star base for a City visit After reading some negative reviews of this hotel was worried about what we would find, after booking a 4-night stay; however was on the whole pleasantly surprised. We arrived at the hotel at about 11.45 p.m. to be greeted by the night porter who as well as giving us our keys spent time giving city maps and explaining how to get to the main attractions. Rooms are adequately furnished, modern with TV, air conditioning and a toilet and bath/shower off. I suppose they could be described as small but were adequate for our city visit. We did find that the wall/floor were thin and noise carried with ease, especially if; as one night someone decided to hold a party at 3 a.m. in the morning! Breakfast in morning was as much as you could eat buffet with cereals, juice, rolls, eggs, bacon etc., As other reviews have pointed out the hotel bar is basically non existent, however we found many local bar within easy walking distance. Clot itself is a small suburb community with many local shops and a market running a small 鈥榩romenade鈥? We actually found a shop selling Gaudi gift items for about a quarter the price of city centre ones. All in all we felt we the Hotel gave us an extremely good value for base for our Barcelona break. 
