<Author>Fluffers
<Content>Very Nice Hotel Just back from a 3 night stay in the hotel with my husband. Very happy with the hotel. Very near the Estacio Nord bus station only 10-15mins in a taxi depending on traffic. Very close to the Metro Station Clot which we used every day. The hotel is within walking distance to Gaudi's Sagrada Familia but you need a taxi to get to the centre of Barcelona only around 鈧? one way. The hotel was very clean, fresh towels every day, very nice buffet breakfast with plenty to eat. The rooms may be classed as a little small but we spent little time in them. Our room was located next to the lift and the corridors had tiled floors so could hear everybody walking to the lift in the morning (A little noisy but then I am a light sleeper). The staff were very friendly and helpful. When we arrived the gentleman on reception asked us if it was our first time to Barcelona and then gave us a map and showed us where all the main sigths were located and the told us the best way to get around. I have a special dietary requirement and he translated some questions I had into Catalonian which I was able to use when we went to eat in restaurants. There are no restaurants or bars near the hotel so you need to go into Barcelona at night to eat but once in La Rambla there are plenty of choices. Avoid the snack bar on the corner near the hotel which we ate in for a quick lunch when we arrived, very poor food and way overpriced. 
