<Content>Would not return While this was a clean, centrally located hotel I was disappointed with the experience. The staff were indifferent (three staff chatting at the breakfast bar, did not acknowledge guests at all). I must say that one of the reception staff was quite good, however, he was the only one of the four who was.The rooms have laminate flooring, which meant that when the people next door to us, above us and on the floor below returned at 2.00 am in the morning, we knew all about it!While not the fault of the hotel, some guests spent an hour running up and down the fire escape, yelling and slamming doors. After a guest complained, the 'gentleman' concerned was much quieter.I don't think I would stay here again.Please note that we stayed over a weekend, it may be much more pleasant during the week. 
